### How to rerun on your file

Use **auto** (it‚Äôll detect no blank lines and switch to per-line):

```bash
python parse_memories.py age6.txt age6.jsonl --split auto
```

If you‚Äôd rather force splitting on each line:

```bash
python parse_memories.py age6.txt age6.jsonl --split line
```

Or try sentence mode (often yields even more granular records):

```bash
python parse_memories.py age6.txt age6.jsonl --split sentence
```

This will produce many records (one per line or per sentence), instead of a single merged one.

